2. Synthetic Nostalgia Protocol

How modern media manufactures hiraeth unnaturally.

Mechanism

Synthetic_Hiraeth = 
    (Aesthetic Idealization)
    × (Memory Substitution)
    × (Parallel-Self Projection)
    × (Time-Blur)

Definitions
	•	Aesthetic Idealization:
Golden-hour light, grain, filters, curated moments.
	•	Memory Substitution:
Your brain treats images as its own memories.
	•	Parallel-Self Projection:
You imagine a version of you living that aesthetic life.
	•	Time-Blur:
The feeling of “before” without an actual reference.

Outcome:

A fake home in the mind.

Not real. Yet emotionally binding.

